05822nam a22009855i 9783035614213DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20172017sz     fo  d z      eng d  a97830356142137 a10.1515/97830356142132doi  a(DE-B1597)481814  a(OCoLC)999372792  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH04a724.62231 aHovestadt, Ludger, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut12aA Genius Planet :bEnergy: From Scarcity to Abundance – a Radical Pathway /cVera Bühlmann, Sebastian Michael, Ludger Hovestadt. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2017] 4c©2017  a1 online resource (264 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aApplied Virtuality Book Series ,x2196-3118 ;v1100tFrontmatter -- tTABLE OF CONTENTS -- tForeword -- tI. Genius -- tII. The Task in Hand -- tIII. Energy Is Not the Problem -- tIV. A Quick Refresher on Electricity -- tV. The Network: Sharing Power -- tVI. Making it Happen: A Turnkey Technology -- tVII. Three Case Studies -- tVIII. The Bigger Picture -- tIX.A Planet in Crisis: Intellect to the Rescue -- tX.The Outlook: What Next? -- tConclusion -- tAppendix -- tReference0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aImagine a world where the power is always on, where there is not just enough energy, but an abundance of it. Such a world is no Utopia, it is a possible reality. Using indefinitely available sources of energy – especially photovoltaic solar, in combination with others – and networking this energy, much in the way that we have networked information, we can get beyond our current energy ‘crisis’ and resolve it. The world we then find ourselves in is not a world without problems – we will face new challenges on the way – but in terms of energy it is a world of plenty. Rooted in sound theory and based on technology that is available now, A Genius Planet offers an accessible but detailed and insightful perspective on how we can free ourselves from our dependency on natural resources and generate, trade, and use energy in ways that open up the genuine potential that we have at our disposal today.  aLondon wurde wegen des Verkehrs Ende des 19. Jahrhunderts der Untergang im Pferdemist vorausgesagt. Zeitgenössische Lösungsansätze dieser ersten Umweltprobleme griffen zu kurz. Dann tauchte der Verbrennungsmotor auf und verdrängte die Pferdefuhrwerke. Inzwischen befindet sich die Menschheit in einer weitaus kritischeren Situation: Im 21. Jahrhundert versucht man die quälenden Energie- und Umweltprobleme auf globaler Ebene mit Vorgaben bei Architektur, Verkehr und Industrie zu lindern.Die Autoren zeigen, dass wir heute jedoch auf bereits vorhandene Technologien zurückgreifen könnten, die die Energieprobleme umweltfreundlich lösen. Erstaunlicherweise ist das Problem nicht die technische Machbarkeit, denn diese ist wissenschaftlich belegt, sondern der Mensch, der das Limit setzt.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEnergy consumption. 0aEnergy development. 0aPower resources. 0aRenewable energy sources. 4aArchitecture. 4aArchitektur. 4aEnergie. 4aEnergy. 4aEnvironment. 4aUmwelt.1 aBühlmann, Vera, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMichael, Sebastian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2017z9783110547719oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruy